The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Negi is third

Kirishi: Grandmaster Parimarjan Negi finished third in the World Youth Star chess tournament after losing the final round to GM Sergei Zhigalko of Belarus. 

World junior champion Zaven Andriasian (Armenia), who was overnight joint leader with Negi, also suffered defeat at the hands of Rauf Mamedov of Azerbaijan. 

The losses of tournament leaders in the final round paved the way for Mamedov and top seed Ian Nepomniachtchi of Russia to finish in a four-way tie at the top on seven points each. In the final round game, Nepomniachtchi drew with GM Yuriy Kuzubov of Ukraine. 

The final standings were decided through the tie-break scores and Nepomniachtchi was declared winner while Mamedov, who was the only undefeated player in the tournament, finished second. Negi and Andriasian finished third and fourth respectively. 

Overall, it was a fine outing for youngest participant Negi in the event that featured some of the finest talents in the world. Negi lost two games, won five and drew the remaining four to pocket seven points. The Indian stands to gain around 15 Elo rating points. 

In the final game, Negi was caught off guard in the opening itself. It was a side variation in the Sicilian defence. 

